🔎 What is Google Colab?
Google Colab (Colaboratory) is a free online tool provided by Google that lets you write and run Python code in your browser — just like Jupyter Notebooks.

✅ Why Use Google Colab?
🟢 No installation needed – Just open a browser!

💾 Free access to GPUs – Great for data science and machine learning

☁️ Cloud-based – Work from anywhere and save your work in Google Drive

👥 Shareable – Easily collaborate like Google Docs

🛠 How to Use Google Colab
Go to 👉 https://colab.research.google.com

Sign in with your Google account

You can:

📂 Open .ipynb files from your computer or GitHub

📝 Create a new notebook from scratch

Click "▶️" Run on each cell to execute Python code

Use Shift + Enter to run cells quickly

🧠 Example Use Cases
Learn and practice Python

Do data analysis with Pandas

Visualize data with Matplotlib or Seaborn

Build and train ML models with Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, or PyTorch
